import{_ as e,o as t,c as o,N as i}from"./chunks/framework.cd9250a1.js";const y=JSON.parse('{"title":"","description":"","frontmatter":{},"headers":[],"relativePath":"english/cambly/preparation.md"}'),a={name:"english/cambly/preparation.md"},n=i("<ul><li><p>Do you think online gaming is a social activity? Why or why not?</p><p>I believe online gaming is a social activity.</p><p>As for me, when I start a new game, I can always make some new friends in-game.</p><p>We play together and exchange contact information.</p><p>Even though we are not playing that game anymore, we remain friends.</p><p>When new games come out, we discuss them and play against each other.</p><p>Online games attract players from around the world, providing opportunities for communication with individuals from diverse cultural backgrounds.</p><p>This cross-cultural exchange fosters an open environment for understanding, friendship, and respect.</p><p>Some online games offer social platforms or forums where players can communicate, share game experiences and tips, and even participate in community activities.</p><p>These platforms provide players with a gathering place based on shared interests and facilitate broader social interactions.</p></li><li><p>Why do you think social activities are popular among adults?</p><p>Humans are social animals, and nowadays adults cannot avoid the need for social interactions.</p><p>当解释原因时，以下是一些常用的英文句式和短语，可以帮助你表达得更有条理：</p><ol><li>&quot;One reason why...&quot; (一个原因是...) Example: One reason why social activities are popular among adults is that they provide an opportunity for human connection.</li><li>&quot;Another factor is...&quot; (另一个因素是...) Example: Another factor contributing to the popularity of social activities among adults is their role in stress relief and relaxation.</li><li>&quot;Furthermore,...&quot; (此外...) Example: Furthermore, social activities offer opportunities for personal growth and development, allowing adults to acquire new skills and expand their horizons.</li><li>&quot;Moreover,...&quot; (此外...) Example: Moreover, engaging in social activities can have a positive impact on adults&#39; emotional well-being by providing a platform for self-expression and support from others.</li><li>&quot;In addition to that,...&quot; (除此之外...) Example: In addition to that, social activities often serve as networking opportunities for adults, enabling them to make valuable connections and explore potential career prospects.</li><li>&quot;Not only... but also...&quot; (不仅...而且...) Example: Not only do social activities fulfill the need for socialization among adults, but they also contribute to their overall personal growth and relaxation.</li><li>&quot;Because of these reasons,...&quot; (由于这些原因...) Example: Because of these reasons, social activities have become increasingly popular among adults as they recognize the benefits of social engagement for their well-being and quality of life.</li></ol></li><li><p>Do you think old people and young people enjoy the same types of social activities?</p></li><li><p>How important is it for you to have social activities?</p></li><li><p>Do you think modern lifestyles give people enough leisure time to spend with others?</p></li><li><p>Do you think people in your country value social activities?</p></li><li><p>Some people would argue that computers will make people more isolated and decrease their social skills. Other people argue that technology will create more social activities. Which opinion do you agree with? Explain your reasons.</p></li><li><p>lmagine you are in this situation and role play with your tutor: One of your friends recently started spending almost all of his time online and started not coming to any of the friends&#39; get-togethers. You texted him to check in but the friend said that he is as social as before but now just online instead of face-to-face. You&#39;re still worried about him and decide to call him.</p></li><li><p>lmagine you are in this situation and role play with your tutor: You have to plan a social activity day for your coworkers (or classmates). lf you could have three social activities that help the group feel closer together. what social activities would you choose and why?</p></li><li><p>What is the best social activity you have done recently? What made the activity special?</p></li><li><p>Some studies say that more engagement in social activities helps the elderly to stay healthier. Why do you think it is the case?</p></li></ul>",1),s=[n];function l(r,p,c,h,u,d){return t(),o("div",null,s)}const f=e(a,[["render",l]]);export{y as __pageData,f as default};
